<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="505" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">M. H. Herbert</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Newport</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>His Majesty’s Government take exception to condition laid down in your
                            note of June 4, and strongly support application for extension of time.
                            I am sending note by post, which should reach you Saturday morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>